  <Name>k__BackingField: Titus
  fancyName: 
  nickname: tit
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Salutation'
      title: Salutation
      number: 1
      content: "  Paul, a bond-servant of God and an apostle (special messenger,
        personally chosen representative) of Jesus Christ, for the faith of God\u2019s
        chosen ones and [to lead and encourage them to recognize and pursue] the
        knowledge of the truth which leads to godliness, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'based on the hope and divine guarantee of eternal life, [the life]
        which God, who is ever truthful and without deceit, promised before the ages
        of time began, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and at the appointed time has made known His word and revealed it
        as His message, through preaching, which was entrusted to me according to
        the command of God our Savior\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Qualifications of Elders'
      title: Qualifications of Elders
      number: 4
      content: 'To Titus, my true child in a common faith: Grace and peace [inner
        calm and spiritual well-being] from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Savior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For this reason I left you behind in Crete, so that you would set
        right what remains unfinished, and appoint elders in every city as I directed
        you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'namely, a man of unquestionable integrity, the husband of one wife,
        having children who believe, not accused of being immoral or rebellious. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For the overseer, as God\u2019s steward, must be blameless, not self-willed,
        not quick-tempered, not addicted to wine, not violent, not greedy for dishonest
        gain [but financially ethical]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he must be hospitable [to believers, as well as strangers], a
        lover of what is good, sensible (upright), fair, devout, self-disciplined
        [above reproach\u2014whether in public or in private]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He must hold firmly to the trustworthy word [of God] as it was taught
        to him, so that he will be able both to give accurate instruction in sound
        [reliable, error-free] doctrine and to refute those who contradict [it by
        explaining their error].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For there are many rebellious men who are empty talkers [just windbags]
        and deceivers; especially those of the circumcision [those Jews who insist
        that Gentile believers must be circumcised and keep the Law in order to be
        saved]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They must be silenced, because they are upsetting whole families
        by teaching things they should not teach for the purpose of dishonest financial
        gain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "One of them [Epimenides, a Cretan], a prophet of their own, said,
        \u201CCretans are always liars, evil beasts, lazy gluttons.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This description is true. So rebuke them sharply so that they will
        be sound in the faith and free from doctrinal error, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'not paying attention to Jewish myths and the commandments and rules
        of men who turn their backs on the truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'To the pure, all things are pure; but to the corrupt and unbelieving,
        nothing is pure; both their mind and their conscience are corrupted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: They profess to know God [to recognize and be acquainted with Him],
        but by their actions they deny and disown Him. They are detestable and disobedient
        and worthless for good work of any kind.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Duties of the Older and Younger'
      title: Duties of the Older and Younger
      number: 1
      content: '  But as for you, teach the things which are in agreement with sound
        doctrine [which produces men and women of good character whose lifestyle
        identifies them as true Christians]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Older men are to be temperate, dignified, sensible, sound in faith,
        in love, in steadfastness [Christlike in character].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Older women similarly are to be reverent in their behavior, not malicious
        gossips nor addicted to much wine, teaching what is right and good, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'so that they may encourage the young women to tenderly love their
        husbands and their children, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'to be sensible, pure, makers of a home [where God is honored], good-natured,
        being subject to their own husbands, so that the word of God will not be
        dishonored.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In a similar way urge the young men to be sensible and self-controlled
        and to behave wisely [taking life seriously]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And in all things show yourself to be an example of good works, with
        purity in doctrine [having the strictest regard for integrity and truth],
        dignified, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'sound and beyond reproach in instruction, so that the opponent [of
        the faith] will be shamed, having nothing bad to say about us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Urge bond-servants to be subject to their own masters in everything,
        to be pleasing and not talk back, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'not stealing [things, regardless of value], but proving themselves
        trustworthy, so that in every respect they will adorn and do credit to the
        teaching of God our Savior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the [remarkable, undeserved] grace of God that brings salvation
        has appeared to all men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'It teaches us to reject ungodliness and worldly (immoral) desires,
        and to live sensible, upright, and godly lives [with a purpose that reflect
        spiritual maturity] in this present age, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'awaiting and confidently expecting the [fulfillment of our] blessed
        hope and the glorious appearing of our great God and Savior, Christ Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'who [willingly] gave Himself [to be crucified] on our behalf to redeem
        us and purchase our freedom from all wickedness, and to purify for Himself
        a chosen and very special people to be His own possession, who are enthusiastic
        for doing what is good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Tell them these things. Encourage and rebuke with full authority.
        Let no one disregard or despise you [conduct yourself and your teaching so
        as to command respect].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Godly Living'
      title: Godly Living
      number: 1
      content: '  Remind people to be subject to rulers and authorities, to be obedient,
        to be ready and willing to do good, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'to slander or abuse no one, to be kind and conciliatory and gentle,
        showing unqualified consideration and courtesy toward everyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For we too once were foolish, disobedient, deceived, enslaved to
        various sinful desires and pleasures, spending and wasting our life in malice
        and envy, hateful, hating one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But when the goodness and kindness of God our Savior and His love
        for mankind appeared [in human form as the Man, Jesus Christ], '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He saved us, not because of any works of righteousness that we have
        done, but because of His own compassion and mercy, by the cleansing of the
        new birth (spiritual transformation, regeneration) and renewing by the Holy
        Spirit, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'whom He poured out richly upon us through Jesus Christ our Savior, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'so that we would be justified [made free of the guilt of sin] by
        His [compassionate, undeserved] grace, and that we would be [acknowledged
        as acceptable to Him and] made heirs of eternal life [actually experiencing
        it] according to our hope (His guarantee). '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'This is a faithful and trustworthy saying; and concerning these things
        I want you to speak with great confidence, so that those who have believed
        God [that is, those who have trusted in, relied on, and accepted Christ Jesus
        as Savior,] will be careful to participate in doing good and honorable things.
        These things are excellent [in themselves] and profitable for the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But avoid foolish and ill-informed and stupid controversies and genealogies
        and dissensions and quarrels about the Law, for they are unprofitable and
        useless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "After a first and second warning reject a divisive man [who promotes
        heresy and causes dissension\u2014ban him from your fellowship and have nothing
        more to do with him], "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Personal Concerns'
      title: Personal Concerns
      number: 11
      content: 'well aware that such a person is twisted and is sinning; he is convicted
        and self-condemned [and is gratified by causing confusion among believers].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When I send Artemas or [perhaps] Tychicus to you, make every effort
        to come to me at Nicopolis, for I have decided to spend the winter there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Do your best to help Zenas the lawyer and Apollos on their way; see
        that they are supplied and lack nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Our people must learn to do good deeds to meet necessary demands
        [whatever the occasion may require], so that they will not be unproductive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: All who are with me greet you. Greet those who love us in the faith. 
        Grace be with all of you.
      comments: []
